## GO enrichment analysis
This folder contains R scripts used to perform Gene Ontology (GO) enrichment analysis by the clusterProfiler R package (Wu et al. 2021).
These analyses were conducted using genes involved in strong interspecies correlations as well as co-expression modules from WGCNA.
- Highly correlated interspecies genes
  - For Sinorhizobia: the top 200 positive and negative correlations
  - For Medicago : the top 200 positive and negative correlations
- Module-wise gene sets
  - Genes belonging to each module from the WGCNA analysis

## Input data
The following input files are required:
- Table in interspecieis correlations generated in the previous "Data_processing" step (defined as CorrMat_table_bSM).
- "Summary_table_SM_model.csv" Module assignment table generated in the previous "WGCNA" step
- "EnrichedGO_highcorr.csv" Table containing enriched GO terms from the highly correlated interspecies genes
- "EnrichedGO_modules_SM_model.csv" Table containing enriched GO terms from the module-wise genes

GO Reference annotations
GO annotations for each species are available from the following sources:
- For Sinorhizobia (available from https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/datasets/genome/GCF_002197065.1/)
  - "GCF_002197065.1_ASM219706v1_genomic.gtf.gz"
- For Medicago (available from https://medicago.toulouse.inra.fr/MtrunA17r5.0-ANR/)
  - "MtrunA17r5.0-ANR-EGN-r1.9.gtf"
  - "MtrunA17r5.0-ANR-EGN-r1.9.b2g.tsv"
  - "MtrunA17r5.0-ANR-EGN-r1.9.xlsx"

## Processing
The scripts in this folder perform the following steps:
- Build GO terminology references for each speices
- Perform GO enrichment analysis
  - for highly correlated interspecies genes
  - for Module-wise genes
- Visualzing the enriched GOs
  - for highly correlated interspecies genes
  - for module-wise genes
